  "text": "A high proportion of \"retirees\" were in an advanced stage of liver disease at enrolment. These persons were probably diagnosed late, since awareness about HCV in older people is low in the general population and among clinicians. Older age is also a risk factor for faster progression of liver disease and cirrhosis [CITATION_1] .",
